    "discriminators": [
     "Friction morphology, but the LOW cousin of a door hinge. Rope under tension groans: quasi-periodic stick-slip near 500-1500 Hz, often with a slow upward pitch drift as the fibres tighten. That drift plus the low centroid is the separation from DOORCreak, which squeals bright at 2-4 kHz with a far more erratic centroid.",
     "Against WOODFric: wood creaks are drier and brighter; rope is fibrous, darker and more tonal (harmonicity ~0.4) because the loaded strand behaves like a stretched string.",
     "Against ROPEMvmt: a creak is loaded rope under static tension; movement is unloaded rope travelling across a surface (a zuzz or a zipline)."
    ],
    "confusable_with": [
     "DOORCreak",
     "WOODFric",
     "ROPEMvmt",
     "METALFric"
    ]
   }
