    "discriminators": [
     "The deadest impact in the whole material set. A rope slap or a coil dropped on a deck has an instant attack and essentially NO ring — decay_time_seconds_60db near 0.03 s, partial_count near zero. Say the boundary from this side: WOODImpt rings for ~0.1-0.2 s and a METAL impact for ~1 s; rope rings for nothing.",
     "That near-total absence of resonance, plus the broadband slap spectrum, is what makes this narrowable rather than semantic.",
     "Ropes flogging repeatedly in the wind produce a sparse aperiodic impact train and still belong here per the explanation, not in ROPEMvmt."
