    "discriminators": [
     "Rope in transit: the zuzz of a line running over a rail or through a pulley, or a zipline. A sustained, bright, noisy friction bed with low crest factor and near-zero harmonicity; a zipline adds a rising centroid trajectory as speed builds.",
     "Against ROPECreak: movement is unloaded and running — noisy, flat, bright, no stick-slip groan. A creak is loaded and static, far more tonal and much darker.",
     "Against ROPEHndl: movement is the rope travelling under its own momentum; handling is in-hand knotting and coiling, quieter and more granular. The explanation cross-references both directions."
